Geography: Country of Origin Egypt, Fayum Entrance Area, Meidum (Maidum)
Credit Line: Gift of Mrs. G. W. Neville and Miss Cardwell, 1906
Description: The upper part of a stela dedicated to Osiris by a "servant" whose name is lost and his wife, Henutnafret. They are accompanied by a row of worshipers depicted below; the last in line carries a tall-necked jar in the form of the Egyptian hieroglyph for good." Though much damaged, the stela is well executed in a fine, linear style.
Provenance: Received with a group of material described as excavated at Meidum by John Cardwell 1886-1889 under a permit granted by Tawfik Pasha, and received in partage. Donated to the museum by his daughters in 1906.
